# Steps of my solution 
First I defined a variable ```count``` and I updated as it iterates through the array.

Then when I encounters a new character, it writes the compressed representation of the previous character **if necessary** and resets the count to 1

If the count of consecutive occurrences is greater than 1, but less than 10, it writes the compressed representation of the previous character followed by the count as a string.
