# Approach
Just traverse on the given chars array length .Use one while loop to calculate the number of time the particular character is repeating.
**Now after getting the count , We have 3 cases**
1. When count is ==1 means single character so just add them in chars array and increase the j pointer further (j++)
2. when the count value is <=9 means single digit value so we will add the character and then add the value of count like in case(1)
3. Now here the case is when the count is greater than single digit
 Like in case 3 where B is 12 times so here we have convert it in the string and loop on it and add character by character like "1" "2" 

So when our traversal end the value of the j variable is our answer as the final length of the new chars array with compressed string.

# **This solution beats 98%**

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
**O(n)** as there is only single traversal over the chars array is done 

- Space complexity:
**O(1)** or constant as no extra data structure is required

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int compress(char[] chars) {

        int n=chars.length;
        int j=0,i=0;
       if(chars.length==1)return 1;
       // base case as if length is 1 than new length will be 1 only 
       while(i<n){
           // traversing the character length array 
           char charac = chars[i];
           int count=1;
           while(i+1<n&&chars[i]==chars[i+1]){
               // in this we are simply counting number of duplicates like 
            //    how many time there is a character is repeated 
               count++;
               i++;
           }
           // if character is present 1 time only than just add the character
           if(count<=1){
               chars[j++]=charac;
           }
           // as when count of character is more than 1 
           else{
           String ans =count+"";
           // creating string for updating when the count is greater than 9 like 

           if(ans.length()==1){
                chars[j++]=charac;
                chars[j++]=ans.charAt(0);
           }
           // case 3 where b is 12 times repeated
           else{
               chars[j++]=charac;
               for(int p=0;p<ans.length();p++){
                   chars[j++]=ans.charAt(p);
               }
           }
           }
           i++;
       }
        // returning the new value of the new chars array length;
      return j;
    }
}
```
