# Approach
Initialize variables: ansindex to keep track of the current index in the compressed vector, i to iterate through the original vector, and n to store the size of the original vector.

Use a while loop to iterate through the original vector chars.

Find the end of the repeating sequence: Start another loop (j) from i+1 until either the end of the vector or until the character at index j is different from the character at index i.

Store the character at i in the compressed vector at index ansindex and increment ansindex.

Calculate the count of the repeating characters: count is the difference between j and i, representing the number of times the character at index i is repeated in the original vector.

If count is greater than 1, it means there are consecutive repeated characters. In this case, convert count to a string representation (cnt) using to_string() and loop through each character in cnt.

For each character in cnt, store it in the compressed vector at index ansindex and increment ansindex.

Update i to the value of j to move to the next character in the original vector.

Repeat steps 3 to 8 until all characters in the original vector have been processed.

Return ansindex, which represents the size of the compressed vector.
