# INTUITION 
We are asked to compress the string by replacing multiple same characters followed by their frequency. if frequency/ count is 1, ignore that and if it is greater than 9, break them in sperate characters. See how to tackle this.

# APPROACH
1. DECLARE some variables like **count** to keep tract of frequency of characters, **index** to store character and frequency in array.
2. run a loop till less than size, and set j as i+1.
3. in another loop, check if i and j index are same, if same increase j by 1 unless they are not equal. [**j - i will give the actual frequency of each character**]
4. store the character at index in chars and increase by 1.
5. check if count is greater than 1 or not. if not **set i = j**  so that we can start traversing from next different character.
6. if count is greater than 1, then convert the count into string.
7. using for range based loop, extract character by character from count string and insert it in chars array. like this 
   string temp= to_string(count);
                for(char c: temp)
                    chars[index++]= c;
8. return index as it contains the  new length of chars.

# EXAMPLE-
We dont have to care about what character we are encountering.
["a","a","b","b","b","b","b","b","b","b","b","b","c","c","c"]

in this we are having 2 a, 10 b, 3 c.
try to solve yourself. if you face any problem, feel free to contact me.
# COMPLEXITY 
**TIME** O(N)- LINEAR.
**SPACE** O(1)- CONSTANT
# CODE
```
class Solution {
public:
    int compress(vector<char>& chars) {
        int size= chars.size();
        int i=0, j=0, count=0, index=0;
        while(i<size){
            j= i+1;
            while((j<size)&&(chars[i]==chars[j]))
                j=j+1;
            //storing character and setting up count
            chars[index++]= chars[i];
            count= j-i;
            if(count>1)
            {
                string temp= to_string(count);
                for(char c: temp)
                    chars[index++]= c;
            }
            i=j;
        }
        return index;   
    }
};
```

