# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
The intuition behind the code is to compress the given array of characters by counting consecutive repeating characters. If the count of a character is greater than 1, append the character followed by the count to the resulting compressed array.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
**Two Pointer**
Initialize a counter cnt to 1 and a pointer j to 0.
If the size of the input array chars is 1, return 1 (no compression needed for a single character).
Iterate through the chars array starting from index 1.
For each element, compare it with the previous element. If they are the same, increment the counter cnt.
If the current element is different from the previous element or it's the last element in the array, update the chars[j] with the previous character (since it's the end of a group).
If the count cnt is greater than 1, convert it to a string c using to_string(cnt).
Iterate through each character in the string c and append them to the chars array starting from index j+1.
Increment j by the number of characters appended in step 7.
Repeat steps 4-8 until all elements in the chars array are processed.
Return the updated pointer j, which represents the new length of the compressed array.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(N)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
The time complexity of the code is O(N), where N is the size of the input array chars. This is because we iterate through each element in the array once.

- Space complexity: O(1)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
The space complexity is O(1) because the code uses only a constant amount of extra space to store the counters and pointers.

# Code
```Java []
class Solution {
    public int compress(char[] chars) {
        int cnt = 1;
        int j = 0;

        if (chars.length == 1)
            return 1;

        for (int i = 1; i <= chars.length; i++) {
            cnt = 1;
            while (i < chars.length && chars[i] == chars[i - 1]) {
                cnt++;
                i++;
            }
            chars[j++] = chars[i - 1];

            if (cnt > 1) {
                String c = String.valueOf(cnt);
                for (char ch : c.toCharArray()) {
                    chars[j++] = ch;
                }
            }
        }

        return j;
    }
}
```
